1 cassandra.yaml

before
AllowAllAuthenticator
after
PasswordAuthenticator

2. standart users
run cqlsh.bat :
cqlsh -u cassandra -p cassandra
3. add new user
CREATE ROLE sa WITH PASSWORD = '123456' AND SUPERUSER = true AND LOGIN = true;
--
Log in as the newly created superuser:
  cqlsh -u <new_super_user> -p <some_secure_password>

  Fetching role authentication can be a costly operation. To decrease the burden, adjust the validity period for role caching with the roles_validity_in_ms option in the cassandra.yaml file (default 2000 milliseconds):
  roles_validity_in_ms: 2000

  Configure the refresh interval for role caches by setting the roles_update_interval_in_ms option in the cassandra.yaml file (default 2000 ms):
  roles_update_interval_in_ms: 2000

  https://docs.datastax.com/en/cassandra/3.0/cassandra/configuration/secureConfigNativeAuth.html
  *****************************************************
  Query the defined keyspaces using the SELECT statement.
   SELECT * FROM system.schema_keyspaces;